-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 06:00AM EDT
-- None



March 17 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Monday:

** Vodafone Group Plc <VOD.L> has agreed to buy Spain's largest cable operator Ono for 7.2 billion euros ($10 billion), in the latest move by the British group to rebuild its European operations with a broadband offering. [ID:nL6N0ME17B]  ** Germany's debt-burdened utility RWE <RWEG.DE> has struck a deal to sell its oil and gas production arm DEA [RWEDE.UL] to a group of investors led by Russian tycoon Mikhail Fridman, valuing the unit at about 5.1 billion euros ($7.10 billion) including debt. [ID:nL6N0MD0N8]  ** French ship supplier Bourbon <GPBN.PA> said its main shareholder, Jaccar Holdings [JACCA.UL], was planning to make an offer to buy the company. The offer is conditional upon Jaccar obtaining 50.1 percent of the capital, as well as bank financing, Bourbon said in a statement. [ID:nL6N0ME129]  ** Russia's top oil producer Rosneft <ROSN.MM> is set to acquire an indirect stake in Pirelli <PECI.MI> after reaching an outline deal with a group of shareholders in the Italian tire maker valuing its shares at 12 euros each.  ** French state-owned bank Caisse des Depots (CDC) could reduce its 8.85 percent stake in waste and water group Veolia <VIE.PA>, CDC head Jean-Pierre Jouyet told the Les Echos newspaper in an interview published on Monday. [ID:nL6N0ME1BD]  ** Canadian oil and gas producer Encana Corp <ECA.TO> is in advanced talks to sell its Wyoming natural gas field to private-equity firms Carlyle Group LP <CG.O> and NGP Energy Capital Management LLC for about $2 billion, the Wall Street Journal reported on Sunday, citing unnamed sources. [ID:nL2N0ME00U]  ** Giant Investment Ltd will acquire Chinese online gaming company Giant Interactive Group Inc <GA.N> for $3 billion and take it private, the companies said on Sunday. [ID:nL2N0MD0M3]  ** Italy's biggest bank by assets UniCredit SpA <CRDI.MI> plans to sell or float its Pioneer Investments asset management unit, valued at over 2 billion euros ($2.79 billion), as part of a wider disposal program, the Financial Times reported. [ID:nL3N0MD0F2]  ** Italian insurer Unipol <UNPI.MI> agreed on Saturday to sell assets with premiums worth about 1.1 billion euros ($1.53 billion) to Germany's Allianz <AVLG.DE>, a move it said would allow it to comply with Italian regulators. [ID:nL6N0MC0O8]